<TITLE> Weather 'to break', monsoon rains forecast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 20 (bdnews24.com)The met office forecast long-awaited rain over the next 24 hours, as monsoon winds gained strength over the Bay of Bengal on Saturday. Senior met officer SM Mahmudul Huq told bdnews24.com, "The monsoon over the north Bay, which has become active, will intensify over the next 24 hours with the possibility of rainfall in different places of the country." "The prevailing heat and humidity will be relieved with the rainfall." He said the monsoon could cover the whole of the country in the next few days. The highest temperature in the capital on Saturday was 35.6 degrees Celsius. The country's highest temperature registered in Rajshahi, at 37.5 degrees Celsius, while Faridpur had the lowest temperature at 22.4 degrees Celsius. Chittagong, Sylhet and Barisal and some places in Rajshahi, Khulna and Dhaka divisions may see squally winds with downpours and thunderstorms on Sunday. The 'mild heatwave' over Rajshahi, Iswardi and Jessore may abate. The met office advised maritime ports to hoist cautionary signal number 3 in the morning but by 5pm it gave the all-clear to lower the signal. bdnews
